1
00:02:00,180 --> 00:02:02,420
You haven't washed in three days, your head is all greasy.

2
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:06,459
What are you watching?

3
00:02:06,780 --> 00:02:07,620
You don't even have any hair.

4
00:02:07,620 --> 00:02:09,379
I don't know why you even bother washing.

5
00:02:11,139 --> 00:02:11,939
Don't.

6
00:02:12,159 --> 00:02:13,259
I'm watching this right now.

7
00:02:13,379 --> 00:02:14,500
I don't understand that one.

8
00:02:15,219 --> 00:02:16,620
We can both understand this one.

9
00:02:17,219 --> 00:02:18,819
Seek common ground while reserving differences, get it?

10
00:02:18,819 --> 00:02:20,099
I don't. Give it to me now.

11
00:02:20,099 --> 00:02:20,699
Stop it.

12
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,219
The TV is public property.

13
00:02:22,219 --> 00:02:23,340
It's not just yours.

14
00:02:23,340 --> 00:02:24,020
What are you doing?

15
00:02:24,020 --> 00:02:25,099
Trying to hog it all?

16
00:02:25,139 --> 00:02:26,979
Is that even relevant?

17
00:02:27,580 --> 00:02:28,500
Give it to me, quick.

18
00:02:28,539 --> 00:02:29,580
I haven't finished watching yet.

19
00:02:29,580 --> 00:02:30,219
Go ahead and watch.

20
00:02:30,219 --> 00:02:31,379
No one is stopping you.

21
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:33,620
I want to watch the program that was just on.

22
00:02:34,500 --> 00:02:36,060
Look at you acting all entitled.

23
00:02:36,219 --> 00:02:37,099
What do you want?

24
00:02:37,379 --> 00:02:38,860
You think you can just watch whatever you want?

25
00:02:38,860 --> 00:02:40,379
Who do you think you are?

26
00:02:40,379 --> 00:02:41,099
No...

27
00:02:42,340 --> 00:02:43,939
You are simply unreasonable.

28
00:02:47,699 --> 00:02:49,340
Surrendering so soon?

29
00:02:49,780 --> 00:02:51,259
That's not your style.

30
00:02:52,139 --> 00:02:54,180
You should at least put up a fight.

31
00:02:54,819 --> 00:02:56,300
Let's watch together, together.

32
00:02:56,860 --> 00:02:58,939
I won't wallow in the mire with you.

33
00:02:59,099 --> 00:03:01,060
How can you call it wallowing in the mire?

34
00:03:01,620 --> 00:03:03,340
You should say we're birds of a feather.

35
00:03:04,139 --> 00:03:04,939
That's not right either.

36
00:03:06,379 --> 00:03:07,259
It should be...

37
00:03:08,020 --> 00:03:09,060
Shared interests.

38
00:03:09,259 --> 00:03:10,060
You?

39
00:03:10,620 --> 00:03:12,180
Share interests with me?

40
00:03:12,180 --> 00:03:14,020
You're really overestimating yourself.

41
00:03:28,860 --> 00:03:29,479
What are you doing?

42
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,340
What is wrong with you?

43
00:03:30,979 --> 00:03:33,099
Stealing my book is like killing my father!

44
00:03:33,180 --> 00:03:34,139
Give me a break.

45
00:03:34,819 --> 00:03:36,219
Your parents died ages ago.

46
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:38,860
It should be "stealing one's wife."

47
00:03:39,180 --> 00:03:39,979
That's not right either.

48
00:03:40,159 --> 00:03:41,460
You don't have a wife or kids.

49
00:03:42,060 --> 00:03:43,479
It's a metaphor!

50
00:03:43,740 --> 00:03:44,780
It means...

51
00:03:45,419 --> 00:03:46,219
Forget it.

52
00:03:46,539 --> 00:03:48,060
I can't teach a blockhead like you.

53
00:03:48,419 --> 00:03:49,340
Then let me teach you.

54
00:03:49,539 --> 00:03:50,620
You teach me?

55
00:03:51,180 --> 00:03:52,139
What a joke.

56
00:03:52,139 --> 00:03:53,979
I'm a professor from a top university.

57
00:03:54,139 --> 00:03:55,259
Retired.

58
00:03:55,259 --> 00:03:57,060
You're just an uncultured boor.

59
00:03:57,180 --> 00:03:59,460
I went to college too.

60
00:03:59,460 --> 00:04:00,740
The "commune-to-commune" kind.

61
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:02,699
In my eyes, you're just illiterate.

62
00:04:02,919 --> 00:04:03,500
Fine.

63
00:04:03,659 --> 00:04:05,219
Even if I'm not as learned as you,

64
00:04:06,780 --> 00:04:08,259
I have this in my hand.

65
00:04:10,300 --> 00:04:11,180
I have legs.

66
00:04:12,060 --> 00:04:13,780
What use are legs?

67
00:04:13,939 --> 00:04:15,699
Can legs control the TV?

68
00:04:15,780 --> 00:04:16,819
That would be amazing.

69
00:04:16,819 --> 00:04:18,180
Oh my god.

70
00:04:18,579 --> 00:04:20,459
If I have legs, I can walk away.

71
00:04:20,699 --> 00:04:22,139
I never want to see you again!

72
00:04:22,139 --> 00:04:23,459
You think you can just avoid me?

73
00:04:23,899 --> 00:04:25,220
We live under the same roof.

74
00:04:25,259 --> 00:04:26,220
How can we avoid it?

75
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:29,579
What are you doing?

76
00:04:30,860 --> 00:04:31,699
Li Jianguo.

77
00:04:32,459 --> 00:04:33,819
Death before dishonor.

78
00:04:34,019 --> 00:04:35,980
Translated into Chinese you can understand:

79
00:04:35,980 --> 00:04:37,579
"Even a worm will turn."

80
00:04:38,420 --> 00:04:39,579
Death before dishonor.

81
00:04:39,579 --> 00:04:41,379
I can understand that phrase.

82
00:04:41,379 --> 00:04:42,740
Oh my god.

83
00:04:45,220 --> 00:04:46,019
Xiao Cai.

84
00:04:46,660 --> 00:04:47,660
Someone's knocking.

85
00:04:48,259 --> 00:04:49,060
Coming.

86
00:04:50,980 --> 00:04:51,779
What is it?

87
00:04:51,779 --> 00:04:53,339
Are you reporting a death or something?

88
00:04:54,779 --> 00:04:55,579
Come in.

89
00:04:56,100 --> 00:04:57,259
Professor Fan.

90
00:04:57,899 --> 00:04:58,860
You... you...

91
00:04:59,660 --> 00:05:00,459
What's going on?

92
00:05:00,939 --> 00:05:02,819
Are you moving in right now?

93
00:05:02,819 --> 00:05:04,620
Oh, I'm a bit of a third wheel.

94
00:05:04,660 --> 00:05:06,980
Should I clear out for you?

95
00:05:07,180 --> 00:05:08,100
Xiao Cai.

96
00:05:08,379 --> 00:05:09,660
Don't talk nonsense.

97
00:05:10,100 --> 00:05:11,980
Who knows who'll be the one clearing out.

98
00:05:12,100 --> 00:05:12,980
Professor Fan.

99
00:05:13,339 --> 00:05:14,540
Is something the matter?

100
00:05:14,860 --> 00:05:16,339
Or who are you looking for?

101
00:05:18,480 --> 00:05:19,819
Look, look, Xiao Cai.

102
00:05:20,939 --> 00:05:23,379
Professor Fan, you're not mistaken, are you?

103
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:25,300
You're skipping the beautiful Ms. Liu,

104
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,180
and looking for me?

105
00:05:26,259 --> 00:05:27,060
This matter...

106
00:05:27,060 --> 00:05:28,379
I have to discuss it with you.

107
00:05:28,699 --> 00:05:29,899
Ms. Liu won't do.

108
00:05:32,420 --> 00:05:33,740
What exactly is the matter?

109
00:05:34,300 --> 00:05:35,620
I want to move to a different place.

110
00:05:37,180 --> 00:05:38,279
Swap with whom?

111
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:39,019
Anyone will do.

112
00:05:39,259 --> 00:05:40,100
Even if you kill me,

113
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:41,779
I won't live with Li Jianguo anymore.

114
00:05:43,779 --> 00:05:45,100
I've had enough.

115
00:05:45,220 --> 00:05:46,500
It's unbearable.

116
00:05:46,540 --> 00:05:47,420
To live with him,

117
00:05:47,620 --> 00:05:48,420
I'd rather die.

118
00:05:49,779 --> 00:05:50,819
Sit on my bed.

119
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,800
Wait a moment.

120
00:05:54,079 --> 00:05:55,439
I don't quite understand.

121
00:05:55,439 --> 00:05:58,439
Since Mr. Li and Mr. Fan have a conflict,

122
00:05:58,680 --> 00:06:01,319
why don't you go resolve this conflict?

123
00:06:01,399 --> 00:06:03,040
I am resolving the conflict.

124
00:06:03,319 --> 00:06:04,600
I'm working hard on it.

125
00:06:04,600 --> 00:06:04,879
No,

126
00:06:04,879 --> 00:06:05,839
I came to find you

127
00:06:05,839 --> 00:06:07,920
precisely to resolve this conflict.

128
00:06:08,079 --> 00:06:10,319
But Mr. Li and I

129
00:06:10,319 --> 00:06:12,720
have never had a conflict between us.

130
00:06:12,860 --> 00:06:14,800
Yes, so...

131
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,560
Professor Fan wants to swap with you.

132
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:18,160
He, well, moves in here with you.

133
00:06:19,519 --> 00:06:20,600
The two of them,

134
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:21,420
won't see each other,

135
00:06:21,420 --> 00:06:22,879
so they won't be able to quarrel, right?

136
00:06:23,040 --> 00:06:24,079
Miss Cai,

137
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:25,519
this method of yours

138
00:06:25,639 --> 00:06:27,199
is not resolving the conflict,

139
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:27,839
but rather

140
00:06:28,319 --> 00:06:29,800
escaping the conflict.

141
00:06:30,480 --> 00:06:32,439
To resolve a conflict,

142
00:06:32,439 --> 00:06:33,120
well,

143
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:35,300
one should first find a conflict.

144
00:06:35,959 --> 00:06:36,759
No,

145
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,000
I mean,

146
00:06:38,399 --> 00:06:39,199
first

147
00:06:39,879 --> 00:06:41,439
identify the conflict,

148
00:06:41,439 --> 00:06:42,240
then

149
00:06:42,720 --> 00:06:45,519
resolve it from a logical level.

150
00:06:45,879 --> 00:06:47,519
Just give me a straight answer.

151
00:06:47,519 --> 00:06:49,680
Are you willing to swap or not?

152
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,519
This

153
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:55,160
requires Mr. Fan himself

154
00:06:55,759 --> 00:06:57,959
to come and negotiate with me.

155
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:58,939
Good heavens,

156
00:06:58,939 --> 00:06:59,720
it's not two countries sending troops,

157
00:06:59,720 --> 00:07:01,160
why do we need negotiations?

158
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:02,279
How about this,

159
00:07:02,920 --> 00:07:05,000
whatever you want to negotiate, talk to me.

160
00:07:05,240 --> 00:07:07,120
I am now Professor Fan's

161
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:08,199
plenipotentiary ambassador.

162
00:07:08,439 --> 00:07:10,819
Then please show me his authorization,

163
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,399
let me see it.

164
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,600
I still need authorization?

165
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:15,420
Is verbal okay?

166
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,800
Authorization is necessary.

167
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,120
It must be written,

168
00:07:19,279 --> 00:07:23,319
and have his personal signature to be valid.

169
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:26,639
Anyway, where is he right now?

170
00:07:27,399 --> 00:07:28,720
Ms. Liu took him outside

171
00:07:28,720 --> 00:07:30,240
to negotiate with others.

172
00:07:30,639 --> 00:07:32,720
We have to walk on two legs.

173
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:34,980
We can't hang ourselves on a single tree.

174
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:37,079
Why hang himself?

175
00:07:38,360 --> 00:07:39,839
Does he want to commit suicide?

176
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:43,480
Later,

177
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,439
the Eighth Route Army's armed working team

178
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:48,720
completely annihilated this group of devils.

179
00:07:49,079 --> 00:07:49,879
It's just that

180
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,920
our Comrade Fan

181
00:07:51,959 --> 00:07:52,920
suffered heavy...

182
00:07:53,959 --> 00:07:55,240
suffered light injuries.

183
00:07:56,279 --> 00:07:57,839
The military sub-district commander decided

184
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:00,519
to let him stay here with you temporarily.

185
00:08:00,759 --> 00:08:02,360
After his injuries heal,

186
00:08:02,360 --> 00:08:04,839
let him go find the troops.

187
00:08:05,240 --> 00:08:07,339
This person looks so familiar.

188
00:08:09,399 --> 00:08:10,639
You recognized him?

189
00:08:10,879 --> 00:08:12,759
Easy to recognize with glasses.

190
00:08:13,399 --> 00:08:15,680
Isn't this the devils' interpreter?

191
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:19,279
No,

192
00:08:19,560 --> 00:08:21,759
he is not the devils' interpreter.

193
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:23,319
He is one of us.

194
00:08:29,399 --> 00:08:31,600
Does the military sub-district have other missions?

195
00:08:32,159 --> 00:08:33,080
No more.

196
00:08:33,600 --> 00:08:36,440
Just let him stay here with you for a while.

197
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:37,360
Right.

198
00:08:37,360 --> 00:08:39,600
You must guarantee his safety.

199
00:08:52,799 --> 00:08:54,200
Let me introduce you

200
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:58,159
This is Uncle Gou of our Yangliu New Village

201
00:08:58,519 --> 00:09:00,120
A pioneer in resisting Japan and saving the country

202
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:01,480
And this is

203
00:09:01,639 --> 00:09:02,440
Professor Fan

204
00:09:04,200 --> 00:09:05,360
Where are you hurt?

205
00:09:05,759 --> 00:09:06,720
Let me see

206
00:09:07,080 --> 00:09:09,120
I'll get some herbs to apply on it

207
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:10,480
No, I'm not injured

208
00:09:11,960 --> 00:09:12,759
Internal injuries

209
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:15,519
Uncle Gou

210
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,679
I'm leaving him in your hands

211
00:09:20,679 --> 00:09:21,600
I'm off

212
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,000
Guaranteed to complete the mission

213
00:09:26,519 --> 00:09:27,320
Good

214
00:09:27,639 --> 00:09:29,240
Wait for the day of victory

215
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:33,960
Don't go

216
00:09:33,960 --> 00:09:34,840
Don't leave

217
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:35,960
You're just going to

218
00:09:36,279 --> 00:09:37,200
Hand me over to him?

219
00:09:37,240 --> 00:09:38,639
He is a fortress household

220
00:09:38,759 --> 00:09:39,720
Reliable

221
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,039
Follow me

222
00:10:01,799 --> 00:10:03,960
If you ask me, you shouldn't bother with him

223
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:05,440
Look how old he is

224
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:07,080
Threatening to cut you off at the drop of a hat

225
00:10:07,519 --> 00:10:10,759
He said he wants to find a suitable tree

226
00:10:10,759 --> 00:10:11,559
To hang himself

227
00:10:11,559 --> 00:10:12,919
He's just scaring you

228
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,919
Let him try dying, I'd like to see it

229
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,360
The sky will rain

230
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,480
People want to commit suicide

231
00:10:17,519 --> 00:10:18,480
No one can stop it

232
00:10:18,519 --> 00:10:19,759
That's not quite right, is it?

233
00:10:19,759 --> 00:10:20,600
It should be

234
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,240
The sky will rain

235
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:24,840
Mother hopes to marry again

236
00:10:25,080 --> 00:10:26,360
I know this idiom

237
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,879
Is this an idiom?

238
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:29,600
I suppose so

239
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,639
The sky will rain

240
00:10:30,639 --> 00:10:31,960
A mother will marry

241
00:10:32,240 --> 00:10:33,960
Right, it's about the same as remarriage

242
00:10:40,159 --> 00:10:41,159
Uncle Gou

243
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:42,360
Your house

244
00:10:43,039 --> 00:10:44,159
The fortress household?

245
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:45,679
Seems to be over there

246
00:10:45,679 --> 00:10:46,600
My house

247
00:10:46,799 --> 00:10:48,799
Was burned down by the Japanese devils

248
00:10:48,840 --> 00:10:51,320
I'm not done with those little devils

249
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,000
Uncle Gou

250
00:11:06,639 --> 00:11:08,360
Where are you taking me?

251
00:11:08,679 --> 00:11:09,679
To heal your wounds

252
00:11:09,879 --> 00:11:11,120
Don't expose yourself

253
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:20,000
Uncle Gou

254
00:11:22,279 --> 00:11:23,200
Are you

255
00:11:23,799 --> 00:11:25,480
Playing guerillas with the devils again?

256
00:11:31,159 --> 00:11:32,080
Professor Fan

257
00:11:32,240 --> 00:11:34,440
You joined the resistance team too?

258
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,360
You brought another one out

259
00:11:58,879 --> 00:12:00,080
Where is this?

260
00:12:00,559 --> 00:12:02,039
Why don't I recognize it?

261
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:02,720
Then

262
00:12:02,759 --> 00:12:03,779
Then what do we do?

263
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,399
Don't be afraid

264
00:12:08,799 --> 00:12:10,840
We believe in the masses

265
00:12:11,279 --> 00:12:13,440
We believe in the organization

266
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:15,279
Any difficulty can be...

267
00:12:16,720 --> 00:12:17,799
So what do we do?

268
00:12:21,120 --> 00:12:23,639
I remember your house seems to be in that direction

269
00:12:23,759 --> 00:12:25,419
Why don't we go check over there?

270
00:12:26,759 --> 00:12:28,000
You recognize my house?

271
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,720
Why didn't you say so earlier?

272
00:12:31,720 --> 00:12:32,360
Follow up

273
00:12:38,480 --> 00:12:39,179
Forward

274
00:12:39,840 --> 00:12:40,639
Go straight

275
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:46,639
Keep going forward

276
00:12:59,440 --> 00:13:02,200
Comrade Old Fan, don't go

277
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:04,799
It's dangerous outside, there are devils

278
00:13:05,519 --> 00:13:07,120
I won't trouble Uncle Gou

279
00:13:07,519 --> 00:13:08,440
Comrade

280
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,759
My injuries have already healed

281
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,600
I'd better go catch up with the troops

282
00:13:13,039 --> 00:13:15,360
Then you must wait for me to put on my pants

283
00:13:15,360 --> 00:13:17,240
To provide you cover

284
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,799
What are you doing?

285
00:13:22,799 --> 00:13:23,480
Shh

286
00:13:23,879 --> 00:13:25,320
I'm watching out for devils

287
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:26,960
Devils?

288
00:13:27,399 --> 00:13:28,720
Are you talking about me?

289
00:13:29,159 --> 00:13:29,960
No

290
00:13:30,159 --> 00:13:31,480
I meant the Japanese

291
00:13:32,200 --> 00:13:33,399
Can we talk inside?

292
00:13:33,539 --> 00:13:34,679
Come

293
00:13:49,679 --> 00:13:51,240
I just want to change rooms.

294
00:13:51,320 --> 00:13:52,600
That's not too much to ask, is it?

295
00:13:52,639 --> 00:13:55,080
Not at all. That's a very low bar.

296
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:57,759
Even a nobody like Mr. Liang...

297
00:13:57,759 --> 00:14:00,039
...can have a single room.

298
00:14:00,799 --> 00:14:01,840
I believe...

299
00:14:03,279 --> 00:14:04,080
Hey.

300
00:14:04,440 --> 00:14:07,080
You foreigner, why don't you learn the good stuff?

301
00:14:07,240 --> 00:14:09,559
You sure learned how to gossip fast.

302
00:14:09,799 --> 00:14:11,559
I didn't make anything up about you.

303
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,159
It is Professor Fan...

304
00:14:13,159 --> 00:14:15,279
...and his roommate, Mr. Li.

305
00:14:15,279 --> 00:14:16,320
They really are...

306
00:14:16,600 --> 00:14:18,639
...unable to coexist peacefully.

307
00:14:18,679 --> 00:14:21,120
He came here seeking refuge.

308
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:22,000
Is that so?

309
00:14:23,039 --> 00:14:23,840
Lao Fan.

310
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:25,039
What for?

311
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:27,159
It's a long story.

312
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:28,879
Too numerous to mention.

313
00:14:29,960 --> 00:14:30,879
That Lao Li...

314
00:14:31,360 --> 00:14:32,960
He smacks his lips when he eats.

315
00:14:32,960 --> 00:14:34,399
He doesn't wash his hands after using the toilet.

316
00:14:34,840 --> 00:14:35,799
He lectures people all day long.

317
00:14:35,799 --> 00:14:37,080
And he brags whenever he opens his mouth.

318
00:14:38,559 --> 00:14:39,519
Sounds about right.

319
00:14:39,519 --> 00:14:40,399
Who is it?

320
00:14:40,840 --> 00:14:42,080
The main thing is...

321
00:14:42,320 --> 00:14:43,480
When he sleeps...

322
00:14:43,879 --> 00:14:44,879
He snores and makes weird noises.

323
00:14:44,879 --> 00:14:45,759
He talks in his sleep.

324
00:14:46,039 --> 00:14:47,879
He burps, farts, and grinds his teeth.

325
00:14:48,399 --> 00:14:49,519
Who could stand that?

326
00:14:51,960 --> 00:14:53,879
No wonder his wife died early.

327
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:54,960
I reckon...

328
00:14:55,240 --> 00:14:56,879
...she died from lack of sleep.

329
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,440
She must have been exhausted.

330
00:14:59,200 --> 00:15:00,480
That really is unbearable.

331
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:02,480
So, what do you plan to do?

332
00:15:03,320 --> 00:15:04,639
So we decided...

333
00:15:04,759 --> 00:15:07,000
...to ask you and him...

334
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,559
...to swap rooms.

335
00:15:08,639 --> 00:15:10,120
You live with Mr. Li.

336
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:12,879
Darn it.

337
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:15,240
I couldn't stand that either!

338
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:15,899
No...

339
00:15:16,159 --> 00:15:16,840
Besides...

340
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,720
...why are you making decisions for me?

341
00:15:18,720 --> 00:15:19,399
How about...

342
00:15:19,519 --> 00:15:22,039
...let Professor Fan sleep in your bed?

343
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:25,480
Two grown men...

344
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:27,159
...sleeping in the same bed?

345
00:15:27,559 --> 00:15:28,720
Is that appropriate?

346
00:15:28,879 --> 00:15:32,200
Or you could sleep on the living room sofa.

347
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:33,559
Why should I?

348
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:35,360
That's even less appropriate for me.

349
00:15:35,399 --> 00:15:36,480
Alright, you two.

350
00:15:36,799 --> 00:15:37,480
Stop arguing.

351
00:15:37,480 --> 00:15:39,000
I'll sleep on the sofa.

352
00:15:40,080 --> 00:15:41,000
Sleeping anywhere...

353
00:15:41,159 --> 00:15:43,080
...is better than listening to Lao Li snore.

354
00:16:02,440 --> 00:16:03,720
What's that noise?

355
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:05,240
People might think

356
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,080
someone's renovating in the middle of the night.

357
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,159
I thought it was

358
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:10,159
a John Deere tractor.

359
00:16:13,480 --> 00:16:14,360
See that?

360
00:16:14,519 --> 00:16:15,559
As soon as I came out,

361
00:16:15,559 --> 00:16:16,960
he stopped.

362
00:16:17,360 --> 00:16:19,679
I think I played a part.

363
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:28,240
It's worse than snoring.

364
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,519
It sounds

365
00:16:29,519 --> 00:16:31,960
a bit like our German language.

366
00:16:38,639 --> 00:16:40,440
You'd better stick to sleep-talking.

367
00:16:40,519 --> 00:16:41,799
In Germany,

368
00:16:41,840 --> 00:16:43,360
in our folklore,

369
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:45,399
there is something called a werewolf.

370
00:16:45,960 --> 00:16:47,120
It's a werewolf.

371
00:16:48,519 --> 00:16:49,919
On the night of a full moon,

372
00:16:50,320 --> 00:16:51,440
that teeth grinding...

373
00:16:51,879 --> 00:16:53,240
He turns into a wolf

374
00:16:53,399 --> 00:16:54,720
and comes to eat people.

375
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:55,399
Come here.

376
00:16:55,679 --> 00:16:58,000
Come check if the moon is full.

377
00:16:58,279 --> 00:16:59,960
Don't scare people like that.

378
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:01,559
Can we get any sleep tonight?

379
00:17:08,279 --> 00:17:09,319
Morning, you two.

380
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:10,460
Not...

381
00:17:10,460 --> 00:17:11,519
Not as early as you.

382
00:17:11,599 --> 00:17:12,400
Good morning.

383
00:17:12,839 --> 00:17:13,839
What's good about it?

384
00:17:14,180 --> 00:17:15,079
I got up late.

385
00:17:15,599 --> 00:17:17,599
A night without Li Jianguo's snoring

386
00:17:17,599 --> 00:17:19,200
makes for a comfortable sleep.

387
00:17:20,640 --> 00:17:22,599
You slept comfortably all night,

388
00:17:22,599 --> 00:17:23,759
but for us,

389
00:17:23,799 --> 00:17:24,799
it was miserable.

390
00:17:24,799 --> 00:17:25,519
What?

391
00:17:25,599 --> 00:17:27,319
Last night, you...

392
00:17:27,319 --> 00:17:28,519
that snoring...

393
00:17:28,519 --> 00:17:30,359
was extremely loud.

394
00:17:30,559 --> 00:17:31,359
What?

395
00:17:32,059 --> 00:17:32,559
I...

396
00:17:33,119 --> 00:17:34,519
I really snore?

397
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:37,319
I always thought Li Jianguo was slandering me.

398
00:17:37,960 --> 00:17:40,200
No wonder, it's not easy for Li Jianguo either.

399
00:17:40,720 --> 00:17:42,279
Other people are devils.

400
00:17:42,599 --> 00:17:44,359
Other people are devils.

401
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:47,279
That's a famous quote from your German philosopher.

402
00:17:47,279 --> 00:17:48,039
No.

403
00:17:48,079 --> 00:17:50,039
It's the French existentialist master,

404
00:17:50,039 --> 00:17:51,960
Jean-Paul Sartre who said it.

405
00:17:52,400 --> 00:17:53,640
What he meant was,

406
00:17:53,799 --> 00:17:57,920
the people around you are the devils you hate the most.

407
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,680
No, what does he mean?

408
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:04,160
He means I'm a devil too?

409
00:18:04,720 --> 00:18:05,400
Lao Lu!

410
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:06,319
You come back here!

411
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:07,160
Come back!

412
00:18:07,299 --> 00:18:07,640
No, wait...

413
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:08,720
You explain yourself!

414
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:09,960
Who is the devil?

415
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,799
The Empress Dowager has arrived!

416
00:18:15,920 --> 00:18:17,680
The Empress Dowager has arrived!

417
00:18:18,019 --> 00:18:19,039
Come.

418
00:18:20,319 --> 00:18:21,119
Grandma.

419
00:18:22,839 --> 00:18:24,319
Please help mediate.

420
00:18:24,640 --> 00:18:26,839
You two silly children.

421
00:18:27,839 --> 00:18:29,759
The older you get, the less sensible you are.

422
00:18:31,240 --> 00:18:33,220
It's such a small matter.

423
00:18:33,839 --> 00:18:35,200
Isn't it just because...

424
00:18:35,720 --> 00:18:37,000
Because of what again?

425
00:18:37,079 --> 00:18:38,000
Because...

426
00:18:38,839 --> 00:18:39,880
I forgot too.

427
00:18:40,960 --> 00:18:42,079
Exactly.

428
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:43,359
So what?

429
00:18:43,440 --> 00:18:44,359
Is it worth it?

430
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,119
You even want to run

431
00:18:47,279 --> 00:18:48,680
away from home.

432
00:18:49,519 --> 00:18:51,319
I'm telling you,

433
00:18:51,480 --> 00:18:53,440
once you walk into this village,

434
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,279
and live in this courtyard,

435
00:18:55,359 --> 00:18:58,160
we are all one family.

436
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:01,839
We must all get along amicably.

437
00:19:01,839 --> 00:19:03,480
No one is allowed to fuss.

438
00:19:03,920 --> 00:19:05,319
The old lady has spoken.

439
00:19:05,319 --> 00:19:06,299
Hurry up and apologize.

440
00:19:06,539 --> 00:19:07,079
Right.

441
00:19:07,079 --> 00:19:08,839
Don't make the old lady angry.

442
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,400
Brother.

443
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:16,279
I was wrong.

444
00:19:17,319 --> 00:19:18,599
Brother, I was wrong too.

445
00:19:20,359 --> 00:19:23,400
Now those are good children.

446
00:19:23,900 --> 00:19:26,279
Come, hold hands.

447
00:19:27,799 --> 00:19:30,119
Hold hands.

448
00:19:30,279 --> 00:19:32,559
Walk together.

449
00:19:33,240 --> 00:19:35,559
Be happy.

450
00:19:35,720 --> 00:19:37,440
And grow tall.

451
00:19:47,920 --> 00:19:49,000
Help!

452
00:19:49,759 --> 00:19:51,160
I really can't take it anymore.

453
00:19:51,299 --> 00:19:51,920
No.

454
00:19:52,160 --> 00:19:53,440
What's wrong with you now?

455
00:19:53,640 --> 00:19:55,359
Even a statue has a temper!

456
00:19:55,359 --> 00:19:57,319
I really can't stand this Mr. Liang anymore.

457
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:58,480
What happened?

458
00:19:58,680 --> 00:19:59,839
Are you running away from home too?

459
00:19:59,839 --> 00:20:00,380
Yes.

460
00:20:00,839 --> 00:20:02,680
Please help me find a room.

461
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,400
Who is it?

462
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:08,200
Who... who is this?

463
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:09,920
You want to stay at our safe house again?

464
00:20:10,839 --> 00:20:11,440
Um...

465
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:13,400
You...

466
00:20:13,400 --> 00:20:14,160
Oh my.

467
00:20:15,180 --> 00:20:15,740
Oh dear.

468
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:20,119
Isn't this Comrade Norman Bethune?

469
00:20:21,079 --> 00:20:22,559
Who is Norman Bethune?
